# Module ownership. Replace every @org/... placeholder with a real GitHub
# team or username before this matters for review routing — GitHub ignores
# entries that don't resolve to an actual team/user, so an unedited
# placeholder is a silent no-op, not an error.
#
# `php artisan make:module` appends a line here automatically when the
# wizard's "owning team" prompt isn't left blank, so this file grows with
# the module registry instead of drifting from it. Edit by hand for
# anything the wizard didn't cover (Core, existing modules below).

# Platform layer — not a module, owned by whoever maintains the base itself.
/app/Modules/Core/ @org/platform-team
/config/project.php @org/platform-team
/app/Vendor/ @org/platform-team

# Modules present as of this review pass.
/app/Modules/Auth/ @org/platform-team
/app/Modules/User/ @org/platform-team
/app/Modules/Geo/ @org/platform-team
